item.title: CVE-2019-13409|2024-09-16T20:17:31.925Z -- topoo%20technology -- topmeeting
item.description: A SQL injection vulnerability was discovered in TOPMeeting before version 8.8 (2019/08/19). An attacker can use a union based injection query string though a search meeting room feature to get databases schema and username/password.

item.title: CVE-2019-13410|2024-09-16T18:12:58.445Z -- topoo%20technology -- topmeeting
item.description: TOPMeeting before version 8.8 (2019/08/19) shows attendees account and password in front end page that allows an attacker to obtain sensitive information by browsing the source code of the page.
